Just weeks ago the prospects for the North American Free Trade
Agreement (NAFTA) seemed assured. It was supported by the Republican
establishment, the prospective Democratic presidential nominee, and
much of the Democratic Congressional leadership. Now the picture is
clouded. Candidate Perot stresses that NAFTA would send jobs to
Mexico. It is too late to get congressional approval of NAFTA this
year and after the elections the makeup of the House could change,
leaving the sentiment there on trade in doubt. The
environment/farm/labor coalition now has 200 signatories in the house
to a resolution conditioning approval of NAFTA on strong environment
and food safety provisions.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d44"
TYPE="PERDOC"
