SUMMARIZER="A">  

In the California Congressional district of Rep. Bob Matsui, a leading
congressional proponent of the North American Free Trade Agreement
(NAFTA), labor leaders, environmentalists and Perot supporters have
signed a Declaration of War against NAFTA.  Working with a shoestring
budget, the foes of NAFTA have worked for three years to win over the
American public while proponents, mainly the business community, are
spending millions to win over Congress. The opponents believe their
public efforts have turned around several congressmen.  With the
conclusion this week of talks over side agreements, both sides are
prepared to go all out in their respective lobbying efforts.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d44"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="FT933-5709"
SELECTOR="H"
SUMMARIZER="A">  

President Clinton has chosen William Daley, younger brother of Chicago
Mayor Richard M. Daley, to head the task force assigned to get the
North American Free Trade Act (NAFTA) through Congress. Daley is a
smooth-talking behind the scenes operator with long-standing ties with
organized labor. Polls show that two-thirds of the American people do
not support NAFTA and grassroots opposition led by labor groups is
growing. Many Democrats in Congress including some from Illinois are
uncommitted and it is Daley's job to convince moderate Democrats to
back the agreement. He must marshal 73 votes from Democratic
representatives of states standing to gain the most from NAFTA.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d44"
