DOCREF="FT934-8628"
SELECTOR="H"
SUMMARIZER="A">  

A rally in Richmond, Virginia on Saturday against the North American
Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA) drew only 115 demonstrators and lasted
only an hour. The participants, mostly supporters of Ross Perot and
union members, said they wanted to send the message to Virginia's
three wavering congressmen that a "yes" vote on NAFTA in the House on
Wednesday would be "remembered in November." Of Virginia's 11
congressmen three have announced as anti-NAFTA, five in favor, and
three are undecided. One of the anti-NAFTA organizers complained that
President Clinton was buying off undecided congressmen with promises
of projects in their districts.</SUM>

